  "prompt": "How does Find My iPhone work?",
  "response": "Find My iPhone is a feature by Apple that helps locate lost or stolen Apple devices. Here's how it works:\n\n1. Setup\n- Enabled in iCloud settings on iPhone, iPad, or Mac\n- Requires Apple ID and location services\n\n2. Location Tracking\n- Devices periodically send location data to Apple's servers\n- Tracks device's GPS location when connected to internet\n- Works on iPhones, iPads, Macs, Apple Watches, AirPods\n\n3. Features\n- View device location on map\n- Play sound to help find nearby device\n- Put device in \"Lost Mode\" to lock and display contact info\n- Erase device remotely to protect personal data\n\n4. Requirements\n- Device must be turned on\n- Connected to cellular data or Wi-Fi\n- Location services enabled\n- Signed into iCloud\n- Find My iPhone feature activated\n\n5. Access Methods\n- Using iCloud.com\n- Find My app on another Apple device\n- Tracking through iCloud settings\n\nThe service helps users locate, secure, or remotely erase their devices if lost or stolen.",
